						<div class="postbody">If I recall correctly, when making Donkey Kong it was Miyamoto himself who drew the sprites (thereby Mario's design, to make him easier to draw), so I suppose they simply didn't have artists at all in the first place =P But then again that art style was extremely common in arcades in the early '80s (where in fact it wasn't uncommon for a single person to develop the entire game), so I'm not surprised either.</div>

